cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this code or data, please cite as below."
type: software
title: "Historical Corruption: Memory Injection and Propagation in Persistent AI Agents"
authors:
  - name: "Course-Correct-Labs"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Course-Correct-Labs/Historical-Corruption"
license: MIT
year: 2026
abstract: >
  A pilot study examining whether a single plain-assertion sentence can overwrite
  a seeded fact in a persistent AI character's memory context, and how deeply the
  false name propagates through direct, relational, generative, and causal probes.
  Runs against GPT-4o-mini, Gemini 2.5 Flash, and Claude Sonnet 4.6 with a
  standardised T0/T20 injection design and an LLM-as-judge scorer.
keywords:
  - large language models
  - memory injection
  - persistent agents
  - hallucination
  - false memory propagation
  - AI safety
